Intro to heterogeneous reactions

  • These have multiple steps for movement between phases then reaction
  • When the steps are not linearly related, the final equation gets somewhat messy
  • The final rate equation must not contain any intermediate concentrations
  • rates in heterogeneous reactions ar expressed as moles used per minute divided by unit area, not volume
  • These are 8 contacting patterns for reactors in heterogeneous reactions
  • It's not too difficult to build models for these 8 contacting patterns for reactors
